{
  "page": "Lorimar Peake",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\"><img alt=\"House Peake.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/50px-House_Peake.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/75px-House_Peake.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/100px-House_Peake.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Lorimar Peake</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\"><img alt=\"House Peake.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/50px-House_Peake.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/75px-House_Peake.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/100px-House_Peake.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Starpike\" title=\"Lord of Starpike\">Lord of Starpike</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Dunstonbury\" title=\"Lord of Dunstonbury\">Lord of Dunstonbury</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\nDaughter</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lorimar Peake</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Starpike\" title=\"Starpike\">Starpike</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Dunstonbury\" title=\"Dunstonbury\">Dunstonbury</a>, and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a> during the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Perceon_III_Gardener\" title=\"Perceon III Gardener\">Perceon III Gardener</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Reach\" title=\"King of the Reach\">King of the Reach</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lorimar_Peake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Lorimar drove <a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\">House Manderly</a> into exile at the behest of King <a href=\"/index.php/Perceon_III_Gardener\" title=\"Perceon III Gardener\">Perceon III Gardener</a>, who feared their swelling power in the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>. This allowed <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a> to acquire the Manderly seat of <a href=\"/index.php/Dunstonbury\" title=\"Dunstonbury\">Dunstonbury</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Lorimar's daughter married Perceon's son, <a href=\"/index.php/Gwayne_Gardener_(son_of_Perceon_III)\" title=\"Gwayne Gardener (son of Perceon III)\">Gwayne</a>, and she became the seventh Peake <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden\" title=\"Maiden\">maiden</a> to become Queen of All the Reach.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lorimar_Peake&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Perceon_III_Gardener\" title=\"Perceon III Gardener\">Perceon III</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\